Health Authorities Act
Royal Inland Hospital
Amalgamation Regulation
Special resolution defined
1  For the purposes of section 16 (4) (c) of the Health Authorities Act, a special resolution for the Royal Inland Hospital, incorporated under An Act to Incorporate the Royal Inland Hospital, is defined as an approval by a majority of the voting members of the corporation present at a meeting of the membership of the corporation, called for the purpose of approving the amalgamation.

[Provisions of the Health Authorities Act, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 180, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 21]
